text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia unifissilis is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the  Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The erect prickly shrub typically grows to a height of 0.15 to 0.7 metres (0.5 to 2.3 ft). It blooms from July to September and produces yellow flowers.
